column19:
Benefits for users, society and organisations: from education and health, to emotional support {Strengthening mental health [B1]}, to personalisation and automation of complex processes. {Communication and accessibility [B5]}, {Task automation and service scaling [B6]}    - "AI in healthcare has the potential to deliver precision medicine, faster clinical trials, and improved workflow." {Diagnostics, decision-making, and patient care [B1]}
- "AI can improve medical imaging technologies, enhancing the detection, diagnosis, and monitoring of diseases." {Diagnostics, decision-making, and patient care [B1]}. GenAI  can help people obtain information more quickly, e.g. on health issues, thus improving access to knowledge and self-determination. {Access to healthcare knowledge and simplified communication [B1]}
-GenAI has the potential to assist patients, e.g. providing emotional support e.g. chatbots., {Strengthening mental health [B1]}
- Facilitating decision-making processes {Diagnostics, decision-making, and patient care [B1]}
- GenAI can improve the productivity and innovation of organisations by automating tasks {Task automation and service scaling [B6]}
- Creating personalised content and interactions {Communication and accessibility [B5]}

