column23:
-"[...] information systems scholarship should focus on exploring the nature and implications of considering GenAI as a component of broader sociotechnical systems, rather than focusing merely on the technical nature of GenAI itself." {Societal impact of GenAI [F3]}, {Organizational transformations to incorporate GenAI [F2]}

-"Researchers in information systems should consider the broader presence of a system, including the boundary conditions that define its presence and impact within the context of an individual, organization, or society." {User-GenAI interaction design [F1]}, {Societal impact of GenAI [F3]}, {Organizational transformations to incorporate GenAI [F2]}

Challenge 1: "Understand and improve business technology based on GenAI. Design science researchers in information systems will have an opportunity to study technological issues in GenAI applications in business." {Application to specific domains and business sectors [F3]}, {GenAI adoption and acceptance factors [F2]}

Challenge 2: "Understand the impacts of GenAI on individuals including workers and general users. GenAI applications and plug-ins will be increasingly used by business workers and general users, which will require a renewal of many research topics in end user computing in the era of GenAI." {User-GenAI interaction design [F1]}, {The required skills and education [F1]}, {Personalization tailored to the individual user [F1]}, {Demonstrating trustworthiness [F6]}, {Psychological effects of GenAI use on individuals [F1]}, {Definition of GenAI metrics [F5]}, {Security and protection [F6]}

Challenge 3: "Understand the impacts of GenAI on organizations in terms of processes and structures. GenAI will undoubtedly affect the capabilities of IT and individuals, leading to changes in business processes and structures." {GenAI adoption and acceptance factors [F2]}, {Organizational transformations to incorporate GenAI [F2]}, {Formation of hybrid human-AI teams [F2]}

Challenge 4: "Understand inter-organizational impacts. When GenAI permeates organizations, the types of interactions between and among organizations will vary, leading to relationship and interactive changes." {Definition of GenAI metrics [F5]}, {Efficiency and scalability [F6]}

Challenge 5: "Understand mission-critical business domains. Research impacts can be more significant in mission-critical business domains  such as healthcare and finance; therefore, special attention should be paid to these areas." {Application to specific domains and business sectors [F3]}, {The required skills and education [F1]}

Challenge 6: "Understand legal and governance issues. AI can lead to negative outcomes and leading to a dark-side of GenAI, requiring the studies of legal and governance issues." {Regulations and legal issues related to GenAI [F3]}

Challenge 7: "Understand broader societal issues. As GenAI is applied in various business sectors, additional societal issues, such as privacy and security, should be studied." {Ethical use of GenAI [F4]}, {Data privacy protection [F6]}, {Security and protection [F6]}, {Societal impact of GenAI [F3]}, {Effect on job market [F3]}, {Formation of hybrid human-AI teams [F2]}, {Risks introduced by GenAI to societies [F3]}

- What is the extent of automation and job replacement? How do we measure it? Does it create “societal stress?” {Automation of routine tasks [F2]}, {Societal impact of GenAI [F3]}
